.TH BYGG-CLI 1 "bygg-cli @PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bygg-cli \- a command-line interface for bygg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bygg-cli
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIfile\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bygg-cli
is a command-line tool for processing HTML and Markdown files with various formatting options.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \--help, /h
Show this help message.
.TP
.B \-v, \--version, /v
Show the version of bygg-cli.
.TP
.B \-c, \--copyright, /c
Show the copyright information.
.TP
.B \-f, \--formatting, /f, -f=formatting, --formatting=formatting, /f=formatting
Set the formatting type (none, pretty, newline, pseudo).
.TP
.B \-m, \--main, /m
Include a main() function in the output.
.TP
.B \-nm, \--no-main, /nm
Do not include a main() function in the output.
.B \-i, \--input, /i
Set the input type (html, markdown).
.TP
.B \fIfile\fR
The file to read from. If no file is specified, input will be read from stdin.
